<TEXT>
<P>
 THE GARBAGE PRIMER: A Handbook for Citizens by Pamela Murphy for the League of 
Women Voters Education Fund (Lyons & Burford: $12.95; 181 pp., paperback 
original). The numbers are staggering: Every year, Americans produce more than 
200 million tons of trash (not counting the scripts for "Melrose Place"), dump 
about 200 million gallons of used motor oil -- the equivalent of 18 Exxon 
Valdez spills -- into the nation's drains, and discard 242 million tires. This 
clear, well-organized overview examines the ever-increasing problem of waste 
disposal and presents the relative merits of various solutions. An excellent 
starting point for concerned citizens. 
</P>
