<TEXT>
<P>
 AMERICA BY THE NUMBERS: Facts and Figures From the Weighty to the Way-Out by 
Les Krantz (Houghton-Mifflin: $10.95; 231 pp., illustrated, paperback 
original). Krantz's quirky compilation of statistics offers an intriguing 
portrait of the nation. An estimated 41 million Americans have had cosmetic 
surgery (breast augmentation for women is the most common operation); 61% of 
the adult population was married in 1991 versus 72% in 1970; African Americans 
are the least likely to wed -- 37.1% had never been married in 1991. 
Interesting, but the reader should bear in mind that not everything can be 
quantified. 
</P>
