<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLA BREVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOSEF WOODARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FRANK ZAPPA: "THE YELLOW SHARK." Ensemble Modern, conducted by Peter 
Rundel.Barking Pumpkin R2 71600. Beyond and apart from his occasional 
reputation as a willful, antisocial maverick with a love of bad manners, the 
recently deceased Frank Zappa maintained a long -- and mostly unrequited -- 
love affair with the serious 20th-Century music tradition. The fascinating 
fruits of Zappa's orchestral labors are ample on "The Yellow Shark," a suite 
performed with affectionate precision and stylistic elasticity by the Ensemble 
Modern. Virtuosic irreverence and post-serial introspection make for perfect 
bedfellows on this ambitious project, where reference points include Weill, 
Berg, Varese and Zappa's own neo-Dada. A powerful discographic swan song. JOSEF 
WOODARD 
</P>
</TEXT>
