<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Smashing Pumpkins' "Siamese Dream" had a smashing week on The Times' Southern 
California pop album chart, bounding from No. 11 to No. 5. Meanwhile, Snoop 
Doggy Dogg has reason to howl with glee: The rapper's "Doggystyle" not only 
reclaimed the top spot on the pop album and R&B charts, but maintained its lead 
in the rap realm. The way Frank Sinatra's "Duets" album plummeted, from No. 2 
to No. 14 after the holidays, you can only conclude that it was a hugely 
popular Christmas gift. Without the gift-buying market -- or a hit single -- 
can "Duets" rally and return to the Top 10? Don't bet on it. TOP 10 ALBUMS 
