<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK: IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * Jodeci, "Diary of a Mad Band," Jodeci, MCA/Uptown. You've heard it all 
before: the racy bedroom chatter, the anguished pleas to a turned-off mate, the 
giddy declarations of everlasting love.But not quite like this. On its second 
album, this vocal quartet energizes the tired R&B formulas with soulful 
harmonizing and some of the nastiest slow grooves you'll ever hear. A big 
improvement over their excessively dramatic, cliche-ridden first album. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent). DENNIS HUNT 
