<SECTION>
<P>
San Gabriel Valley; Part J; Page 3; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
163 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECTS ARRESTED AFTER FREEWAY CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 16-year-old rammed a car, which he allegedly stole, into two La Verne police 
patrol cars and led officers on a 100-m.p.h. chase on the San Bernardino 
Freeway (10) before his arrest in Baldwin Park after crashing into a parked 
car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The chase began Wednesday about 9:40 p.m. after an officer checking out a 
report of an attempted break-in on a pickup truck spotted the suspects' Camaro 
about half a mile away, La Verne police Lt. Paul Allen said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers from La Verne, West Covina, Baldwin Park and the California Highway 
Patrol followed the car at speeds exceeding 100 m.p.h. until it left the 
freeway and hit a parked car in Baldwin Park, Allen said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, a 16-year-old from Pomona, was arrested along with his two 
15-year-old passengers, also from Pomona. All will be charged with possession 
of stolen property, Allen said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver will also be charged with vehicle theft, felony evading, and 
assault with a deadly weapon, Allen said. 
</P>
