<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman Tina Thompson led four USC players in double figures with 12 points 
and the 10th-ranked Trojans scored seven consecutive points down the stretch to 
defeat Oregon, 47-45, Saturday night at Eugene, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
 After the Ducks' Arianne Boyer missed a free throw, Nicky McCrimmon converted 
a three-point play to put the Trojans (9-1 overall, 2-0 in the Pacific 10 
Conference) ahead for good, 43-41. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ducks are 7-4 and 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Oregon State has asked the Pac-10 to review what an assistant coach called "a 
blatant, premeditated and violent punch" thrown by USC's Lisa Leslie at 
Kristina Lelas during Thursday night's game against the Beavers. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA 76, Oregon State 61 -- Trailing, 57-46, with 6 1/2 minutes to play, the 
Bruins went on a 24-0 run to pull away at Corvallis, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
 Natalie Williams led the Bruins (6-5, 1-1) with 26 points and 13 rebounds. 
Oregon State is 8-3 and 0-2. 
