<P>
$9,000 CAR HAS EVERYTHING, FOR $47,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Hong Kong millionaire wanted to complete his car collection with something 
really special, so he ordered a Mini Cooper fitted with a karaoke machine and 
refrigerator. 
</P>
<P>
 "He said he wanted the most luxurious Mini in the world," said Paul Sibley, 
designer at John Cooper Cars, which specializes in "customizing" the small, 
sporty cars. 
</P>
<P>
 Sibley spent $47,000 on George Wong's $9,000 Mini Cooper, inserting a 
television, video recorder and compact disc player in the walnut dashboard. 
</P>
<P>
 A refrigerator large enough to hold a champagne bottle was built into the 
armrest in the back seat and Sibley also managed to find room for a karaoke 
machine. 
</P>
<P>
 But Sibley was unable to fulfill one of Wong's wishes. "He wanted to put an 
old Bakelite telephone in the door but we couldn't close it," Sibley said. 
