<P>
BARONS HOLD MARINA TO TIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fountain Valley's Sheri Simala made 19 saves, leading a strong defensive 
effort that allowed the Barons to post a 0-0 tie with top-ranked Marina in 
Sunset League girls' soccer at Fountain Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first failure to win for Marina (15-0-1, 2-0-1), which is ranked 
No. 1 in the state.Fountain Valley is 8-5-2, 2-0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sunset League girls' soccer games: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 6, Westminster 1 -- Shauna Itri and Christine Tyler each had two goals 
to lead Edison (13-2-2, 3-0). 
