<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; GONZALEZ, HUNTINGTON BEACH HOLD OFF SERVITE TO WIN, 
54-46 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It wasn't pretty, but Huntington Beach, led by Tony Gonzalez's 18 points and 
13 rebounds, had enough firepower to hold off Servite for a 54-46 Sunset League 
victory Saturday night at Huntington Beach High. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams were tied at halftime, but Huntington Beach outscored Servite, 12-2, 
over a 6-minute, 9-second span in the second half to open a 44-34 lead. The 
Oilers then made nine of 10 free throws in the final two minutes to ice the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach (9-6, 3-0 in league) remained in first place with the 
victory. Servite falls to 9-5, 2-1, and had its seven-game winning streak 
broken. 
</P>
<P>
 "We didn't get it done offensively tonight," Servite Coach Scott Hamilton 
said. "Maybe we were just flat after winning two league games (last) week, I 
don't know. Huntington Beach is a fine team, but we had some opportunities and 
didn't execute." 
</P>
<P>
 Servite shot 30% (13 of 43) from the field, and after David Downs, who had a 
team-high 19 points, scored on a drive to cut Huntington Beach's lead to 35-34 
with 1:56 remaining in the third quarter, the Friars went scoreless for the 
next 5:15. 
</P>
<P>
 During Servite's scoring drought, Gonzalez fed Matt Jones, who had 10 points, 
for a layup to start a 9-0 run. 
</P>
<P>
 Clay Chilcott made a three-pointer and a 12-foot bank shot in the run, pushing 
Huntington Beach's lead to 44-34 with 7:22 remaining.  
</P>
<P>
 Although Servite's defense held Gonzalez, who made 10 of 12 free throws, to 
one second-half shot and 10 points in the final three quarters, the rest of the 
Oilers picked up the slack. 
</P>
<P>
 "Of course, most teams will focus on Tony," Huntington Beach Coach Roy Miller 
said. "But the other kids picked it up tonight and that's what we needed." 
</P>
<P>
 Jones had six points in the third quarter, when the Oilers outscored Servite, 
18-10. Josh Holland had nine points and Matt Malmquist added seven. 
</P>
<P>
 Kristian Vallas had 15 points for Servite, but 6-foot-9 center Mark Seaton was 
limited to five points, making one of 10 shots. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sunset League boys' games: 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 42, Marina 36 -- Daniel Keller had 13 points for Fountain 
Valley (10-4, 2-1). Louis Worthy had 12 points for Marina. 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 74, Westminster 65 -- Micah Kroeger scored 22 points for Edison (8-4, 
1-2). Mark Steele scored 13 points for Westminster (0-3 in league). 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View 55, Santa Ana 46 -- Mike Carney scored 17 points to lead Ocean View 
(8-7, 3-0). Juan Corral had 18 points for Santa Ana (0-3 in league). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Liberty Christian 63, La Verne Lutheran 62 -- Dave Vacarro made two free 
throws with eight seconds left to put Liberty Christian (4-8) ahead by three, 
then blocked a three-pointer in the final seconds. Bob McClung had 27 points, 
including four three-pointers, for the Minutemen. 
</P>
<P>
 Sierra Madre Maranatha 91, Southern California Christian 73 -- Josh Cameron 
scored 38 points to lead SCC (3-9). 
</P>
</TEXT>
