<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; FOUNTAIN VALLEY REGROUPS, DEFEATS NO. 9 MARINA IN 
OVERTIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fountain Valley Coach Carol Strausberg didn't call her team's game Saturday 
against Marina do-or-die, but did admit that after her fifth-ranked Barons were 
upset last week, a second consecutive loss would be almost like having one foot 
in the grave. 
</P>
<P>
 The Barons won in overtime, 44-41, over ninth-ranked Marina (9-5, 2-1 in 
league) in a key Sunset League matchup. 
</P>
<P>
 "With two losses in a row, it would be hard to come back from," Strausberg 
said. "I thought we played with composure to beat them again." 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley (10-4, 2-1) beat the Vikings by two points in the Marina 
tournament en route to the title, but after Marina took a 30-25 lead to open 
the third quarter, it appeared the Vikings were in control. They weren't. Six 
turnovers and an 11-1 run by the Barons followed. Only Norie Nakase's 
three-point basket with 1 minute 15 seconds left and Shandy Robbins' turnaround 
jumper amid three defenders with 19 seconds to go prevented Fountain Valley 
from winning in regulation. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sunset League basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 78, Westminster 59 -- Marie Philman scored 36 points and grabbed 16 
rebounds despite first-half foul trouble as No. 8 Edison (10-4, 1-2) rallied 
from a 36-31 halftime deficit. Philman, who is averaging 29 points, sat out the 
second quarter with three fouls after scoring 15 points in the first. 
</P>
<P>
 Amber Farroux scored 18 points for Westminster (5-9, 0-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View 62, Santa Ana 39 -- Farrah Magee scored 14 points and Becky Fraser 
had 12 rebounds to lead No. 6 Ocean View (11-3, 2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Rosary 50, Huntington Beach 45 -- Jennifer Chey scored 16 points to lead 
Rosary (9-1, 3-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley Christian 52, Orange Lutheran 44 -- Andie Shaffner had 15 
points and 11 rebounds to lead Capistrano Valley Christian (7-5, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Ontario Christian 60, Whittier Christian 57 -- Kara Systma had 21 points and 
Emily Schoneveld scored 19 for Ontario Christian (9-3, 2-1). Alana Kempton had 
a game-high 27 points for Whittier Christian (6-6, 1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 84, El Dorado 37 -- The top-ranked Ladycats (13-0) led, 8-6, 
before a 20-3 run put El Dorado (11-4) on ice. Kiyoko Miller scored 22 points 
and Colleen Hudson had 17. Nicole Erickson had 11, all in the first half. 
Shanna Renken had 17 for El Dorado. MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
