<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; IRVINE WOMEN SHOOT POORLY EARLY, LOSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine made only 19% of its field-goal attempts in the first half and never 
recovered in a 72-58 loss to New Mexico State in Big West Conference women's 
basketball Saturday night in Las Cruces, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
 After making only six of 31 from the field in the first half, the Anteaters 
trailed, 39-15. They outscored the Aggies, 43-33, in the second half, but it 
wasn't nearly enough to erase the deficit. 
</P>
<P>
 Paulina Blunt scored 15 points to lead a balanced attack for New Mexico State 
(9-1, 1-0); Anita Maxwell added 13 points and 16 rebounds. Allah-mi Basheer led 
Irvine (1-9, 0-2) with 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Big West Conference game: 
</P>
<P>
