<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASKETBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SEAN WATERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Manual Arts 69, Venice 48 -- There are several outstanding guards in the 
Coastal Conference, but very few inside players who can match the talents of 
Manual Arts David Rickenbacker. 
</P>
<P>
 Rickenbacker, a 6-foot-5 forward who signed with San Diego State, scored 31 
points as the Toilers won their Coastal Conference opener Friday in only their 
second game at home. 
</P>
<P>
 The Toilers used a two-three trapping zone defense and held Venice to only two 
points in the first quarter. Then Rickenbacker took control inside, scoring 16 
of his team's 18 points in the second quarter as the Toilers took a 29-14 
halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Gondoliers played a zone defense throughout the game, but that did not 
stop Rickenbacker from scoring inside. 
</P>
<P>
 Venice guard Rasheed Hazzard, the son of former UCLA and NBA star Walt 
Hazzard, had 18 points to lead Venice. 
</P>
<P>
 The Toilers played without starting forward John Thompson, who is recovering 
from a sprained right ankle.SEAN WATERS 
