</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASKETBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Belmont 66, Marshall 60 -- Center Jesse Yun scored a game-high 23 points 
Friday in a Northeast League game at Marshall. 
</P>
<P>
 Guard Soon Hong added 22 points for the Sentinels. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 78, Hamilton 70 -- Despite blowing a 20-point halftime-lead, Los 
Angeles hung on to win a Coastal Conference game at Hamilton on Friday. Guard 
Brandon Thomas led all scorers with 18 points and Cedric Gardner chipped in 17. 
Bell 60, Locke 54 -- Freddie Alcala scored the first six points in overtime as 
Bell won its third consecutive Southeastern Conference game at Locke on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Locke sent the game into overtime on Ronald Smith's jump shot. 
</P>
<P>
 Alcala hit a three-point shot to begin overtime. After Locke missed its shot, 
Alcala scored on a layup and was fouled. He hit the free throw to put Bell up 
56-50. Dorsey 83, Banning 79 -- Senior forward Ricky Blackmon poured in 32 
points and had seven steals as Dorsey won a Southern Pacific game at home 
Friday. Dorsey guard Sherwin Morgan, who went 4-for-4 from behind the 
three-point line, scored all of his 13 points in the second half. Roosevelt 71, 
Huntington Park 51 -- Roosevelt held Joe Covarrubias to six points in the first 
half and jumped out to 44-23 halftime lead en route to a Southeastern 
Conference win at home Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Covarrubias finished with 17 points, but Huntington Park did not threaten in 
the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Mario Hernandez had 19 points to lead Roosevelt. After missing nine games with 
sprained right ankle, Roughrider 6-2 forward Gerardo Arangure had 12 points and 
seven rebounds. 
</P>
