<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS; VIDEO STORE WORKER ROBBED AT GUNPOINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man pulled a gun on an Oxnard video-store clerk Saturday, forcing her to 
empty the cash register and her own purse before he fled on foot, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man entered Video Adventures on West Patterson Road about 3 p.m. and asked 
clerk Hea Han for help with a video rental, according to Oxnard police.When Han 
requested the man's rental card, he instead produced a handgun and demanded the 
money from the cash drawer, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 After Han complied, police said the man then searched for more money in the 
store's office. Finding none, he forced Han to empty her purse, and he emptied 
her wallet. 
</P>
<P>
 The man escaped with $170 before police arrived at the store. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
