<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: CRENSHAW; REVITALIZATION OF RIOT AREAS TO BE 
DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Community Redevelopment Agency is sponsoring an open community meeting to 
discuss revitalizing commercial areas that were damaged in the 1992 riots. The 
meeting will begin at 7 p.m. Tuesday at Ascension Lutheran Church, 5820 West 
Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The area targeted includes commercial corridors on Crenshaw Boulevard between 
52nd and 74th streets, on Slauson Avenue between Hillcrest Drive and 2nd 
Avenue, and along 71st Street and Florence Avenue between West Boulevard and 
2nd Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Members of Crenshaw 6, the newly elected Community Advisory Committee for the 
study area, will also attend. The committee was formed to assist the agency in 
developing strategies for retail, commercial and industrial strips in the 
revitalization areas in the sixth and eighth council districts. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 977-1795. 
</P>
