<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 CHARGED IN DEATH OF MAN IN COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles police arrested two young men on suspicion of murder late Friday 
after a sports car they had allegedly stolen smashed into a van, killing a 
passenger. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Menchaca and Juan Hernandez, both 18, were being held in the death of 
a 26-year-old Orange County man, whose name was withheld pending notification 
of next of kin, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 7:30 p.m. Friday, two men approached Brian Kim as he parked his 
Mitsubishi 3000 GT on Marathon Street and took it at gunpoint, Lt. John 
Fletcher said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim called police, and officers spotted the car nearly three hours later and 
began tailing it. 
</P>
<P>
 As the car traveled east on Carroll Street, it slammed into a Dodge van on 
Douglas Street. 
</P>
<P>
 One passenger was thrown from the vehicle and struck his head on a retaining 
wall. He was pronounced dead at the scene, Fletcher said. Two other passengers 
were hospitalized at USC Medical Center, listed in critical but stable 
condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
