MAN BOOKED IN DEATH OF PEDESTRIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Van Nuys man has been booked for vehicular manslaughter in the death of a 
pedestrian on Riverside Drive in Sherman Oaks, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Marsha L. Morse, 52, of Sherman Oaks died just after 9 p.m. Friday in the 
accident that occurred on Riverside just west of Mary Ellen Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Morse had just gotten out of her parked car when she was hit and 
knocked 40 feet by the Cadillac driven by Randolph G. Higgins. 
</P>
<P>
 After striking Morse, Higgins' car continued westbound on Riverside and struck 
three parked cars, said Officer John Baby of the Los Angeles Police 
Department's San Fernando Valley traffic division. 
</P>
<P>
 Higgins, 44, who police said had been drinking, suffered lacerations to the 
right eye. He was booked at Van Nuys Jail, Baby said. 
