<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENVIRONMENT: NOTES ABOUT YOUR SURROUNDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Heisler Park Trip -- A field trip to Heisler Park in Laguna Beach, sponsored 
by the Sea & Sage chapter of the National Audubon Society, will be held 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The park is a great lookout point for sea birds as well as the usual 
shorebirds, grebes, loons, gulls and pelicans.The park's shrubbery also 
attracts a wide variety of land birds. 
</P>
<P>
 The trip will begin at 8 a.m. After visiting the park, the group will work its 
way along the coast to do more bird-watching. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in taking the trip are asked to bring binoculars, a bird book 
and a scope if they have one. They are also advised to wear warm clothing. 
</P>
<P>
 To reach the park, take Coast Highway to Cliff Drive, go south and the park 
will be on the right. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Sea & Sage chapter office at (714) 261-7963. 
</P>
</TEXT>
